devdoc.details: Contains the methods related to disputes. v25Tellor.sol references this library for function's logic.

beginDispute(v25TellorStorage.TellorStor.details: Helps initialize a dispute by assigning it a disputeId when a miner returns a false on the validate array(in v25Tellor.ProofOfWork) it sends the invalidated value information to POS voting

params._minerIndex: the index of the miner that submitted the value being disputed. Since each official value requires 5 miners to submit a value.

proposeFork(v25TellorStorage.TellorStora.details: Allows for a fork to be proposed

tallyVotes(v25TellorStorage.TellorStorag.details: tallies the votes and locks the stake disbursement(currentStatus = 4) if the vote passes

unlockDisputeFee(v25TellorStorage.Tellor.details: Allows disputer to unlock the dispute fee

updateMinDisputeFee(v25TellorStorage.Tel.details: This function upates the minimun dispute fee as a function of the amount of staked miners

updateTellor(v25TellorStorage.TellorStor.details: Updates the v25Tellor address after a proposed fork has  passed the vote and day has gone by without a dispute

params._disputeId: the disputeId for the proposed fork

params._supportsDispute: is the vote (true=the dispute has basis false = vote against dispute)
